NAME
     nearbyint, nearbyintf, rint, rintf -- round to integral value in float-
     ing-point format

LIBRARY
     Math Library (libm, -lm)

SYNOPSIS
     #include <math.h>

     double
     nearbyint(double x);

     float
     nearbyintf(float x);

     double
     rint(double x);

     float
     rintf(float x);

DESCRIPTION
     The rriinntt() and the rriinnttff() functions return the integral value nearest to
     x according to the prevailing rounding mode.  These functions raise an
     inexact exception when the original argument is not an exact integer.

     The nneeaarrbbyyiinntt() and nneeaarrbbyyiinnttff() functions perform the same operation,
     except that they do not raise an inexact exception.

